<appendix id="app.security.docupdates">
 <title>Documentation Updates</title>
 <para>
  This chapter lists content changes for this document since the release of
  &productnamereg; 11 SP3.
 </para>
 <para>
  This manual was updated on the following dates:
 </para>
<!--list of xrefs, latest date sorted upmost-->
 <itemizedlist>
  <listitem>
   <para>
    <xref linkend="sec.security.docupdates.sle12_ga" xrefstyle="SectTitleOnPage"/>
   </para>
  </listitem>
 </itemizedlist>
 <sect1 id="sec.security.docupdates.sle12_ga">
  <title>October 2014 (Initial Release of &productname; 12)</title>

<!--list changes here:
  * use meaningful heading for each topic (<term/>)
  * add xref to respective chapter or section, if possible
  * if a section has been removed from a chapter, add xref to chapter and 
     include the respective section name within<citetitle/> 
  * if a change or new feature has been triggered by a fate entry, 
     add ulink to http://fate.suse.com/<#number>-->

  <variablelist>
<!--list of general issues that apply to all books-->
   <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" 
   href="common_docupdates_general_i.xml"/>
   <varlistentry>
<!--2 Authentication with PAM-->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.pam"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      The <literal>pam_pwcheck</literal> module has been replaced with
      <literal>pam_cracklib</literal> and <literal>pam_pwhistory</literal>.
      Updated chapter to reflect this change.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!--9 Authorization with PolKit-->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.security.policykit"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Updated chapter to reflect major software updates.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.ssh"/>
    </term>
<!--14 SSH: Secure Network Operations-->
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Mentioned that SSH on &productname; makes use of cryptographic
        hardware acceleration if available (Fate#308239).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        New section <xref linkend="sec.ssh.sftp.perms"/> (Fate#312774).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!--17 Managing X.509 Certification  -->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.security.yast_ca"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      The &yast; CA module now allows to export key and certificate into
      different files. See
      <xref
       linkend="sec.security.yast_ca.module.defaults"/>
      (Fate#305490).
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term><xref linkend="cha.apparmor.profiles"/>
    </term>
<!-- 21 Profile Components and Syntax -->
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added short description of supported &aa; profile flags in
        <xref linkend="sec.apparmor.profiles.flags"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Thoroughly explained the syntax and subtle differences in meaning
        for &aa; include statements in
        <xref
         linkend="sec.apparmor.profiles.includes"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
<!-- <listitem>
       <para> Introduced new command line tools <command>aa-disable</command>,
        <command>aa-exec</command>, <command>aa-status</command>,
        <command>aa-notify</command>, and <command>aa-easyprof</command> in
         <xref linkend="sec.apparmor.concept.tools"/> and <xref
         linkend="sec.apparmor.commandline.profiling.summary"/>.</para>
      </listitem>-->
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Introduced extended ways to map a profile: Added
        <xref
         linkend="apparmor.profiles.pattern_matching"/>,
        <xref
         linkend="apparmor.profiles.namespaces"/> and updated
        <xref
         linkend="sec.apparmor.profiles.glob.alias"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added description for new optional <literal>allow</literal> and
        <literal>file</literal> keywords for &aa; profiles in
        <xref
         linkend="sec.apparmor.profiles.perm.file_allow"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added description for new <literal>safe</literal> and
        <literal>unsafe</literal> keywords for &aa; profiles to
        <xref
         linkend="sec.apparmor.profiles.exec.clean.keywords"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        New <literal>PUx/pux</literal> and <literal>CUx/cux</literal>
        profile transitions added in
        <xref
         linkend="sec.apparmor.profiles.exec.fallback"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Added new section
        <xref
         linkend="apparmor.profiles.pattern_matching"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!--25 Profiling Your Web Applications Using ChangeHat-->
    <term><xref linkend="cha.apparmor.hat"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Restructured and completely rewrote
        <xref
         linkend="cha.apparmor.hat"/>.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Removed old content describing the &yast; method.
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Introduced a command line example on creating a hat for the Adminer
        application.
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
<!--Part VI The Linux Audit Framework -->
    <term><xref linkend="part.audit"/>
    </term>
    <listitem>
     <para>
      Numerous small fixes and additions, based on technical feedback.
     </para>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Obsolete Content</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
<!-- FATE#308684: Drop profile generating tools from yast2-apparmor -->
       <para>
        Section <citetitle>Adding a Profile Using the Wizard</citetitle> has
        been removed from <xref linkend="cha.apparmor.yast"/> (Fate#308684).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
<!-- FATE#308683: Drop incident reporting tools from yast2-apparmor -->
       <para>
        Section <citetitle>Updating Profiles from Log Entries</citetitle>
        has been removed from <xref linkend="cha.apparmor.yast"/>
        (Fate#308683).
       </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Chapter <citetitle>Using the Fingerprint Reader</citetitle> has been
        removed from <xref linkend="part.auth"/> (Fate#313128).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
<!--list all bugfixes/doc comments fixes here and add ulink for them-->
   <varlistentry>
    <term>Bugfixes</term>
    <listitem>
     <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
       <para>
        Updated the &aa; documentation to version 2.8 &aa;
        (<ulink
         url="http://bugzilla.novell.com/show_bug.cgi?id=722915"/>).
       </para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
    </listitem>
   </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
 </sect1>
